{
  "video_id": "xmNzUEmFZMg",
  "title": "The science of milk - Jonathan J. O'Sullivan",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 7608.0,
      "end_time": 11880.0,
      "text": "Why do humans drink so much milk?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 11890.0,
      "end_time": 13218.0,
      "text": "And given that all mammals lactate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 13218.0,
      "end_time": 16908.0,
      "text": "why do we favor certain types of milk over others?"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 16908.0,
      "end_time": 18769.0,
      "text": "Milk is the first thing we drink,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 18769.0,
      "end_time": 22378.0,
      "text": "and thanks to developments in the  production and variety of dairy products,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22378.0,
      "end_time": 27990.0,
      "text": "it can take on countless forms for our dietary and sensory well-being."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27990.0,
      "end_time": 32708.0,
      "text": "Milk&#39;s primary function is as a complete source of nutrition for newborns."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32708.0,
      "end_time": 36830.0,
      "text": "In fact, since it has all of the vital nutrients for development and growth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36830.0,
      "end_time": 37644.0,
      "text": "proteins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37645.0,
      "end_time": 38420.0,
      "text": "carbohydrates,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 38420.0,
      "end_time": 39245.0,
      "text": "fats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39245.0,
      "end_time": 40620.0,
      "text": "vitamins and minerals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 40620.0,
      "end_time": 41708.0,
      "text": "and water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 41709.0,
      "end_time": 45280.0,
      "text": "milk is the only thing a baby  even needs to ingest"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 45280.0,
      "end_time": 47619.0,
      "text": "for the first six months of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 47619.0,
      "end_time": 51431.0,
      "text": "The unique makeup of milk can vary depending on factors like species,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 51431.0,
      "end_time": 52330.0,
      "text": "diet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 52330.0,
      "end_time": 53888.0,
      "text": "and location."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 53888.0,
      "end_time": 56000.0,
      "text": "Reindeer of the Arctic Circle,  for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 56000.0,
      "end_time": 59400.0,
      "text": "make energy-dense milk  that&#39;s about 20% fat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 59400.0,
      "end_time": 63700.0,
      "text": "roughly five times more than human or cow&#39;s milk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 63700.0,
      "end_time": 66371.0,
      "text": "to help their young survive the harsh, freezing climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 66371.0,
      "end_time": 68240.0,
      "text": "So how is milk made?"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 68240.0,
      "end_time": 71900.0,
      "text": "In the uniquely mammalian process of lactation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 71100.0,
      "end_time": 75111.0,
      "text": "a special class of milk-secreting cells known as mammocytes"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 75111.0,
      "end_time": 79870.0,
      "text": "line up in a single layer around pear-shaped alveoli."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 79870.0,
      "end_time": 83910.0,
      "text": "Those cells absorb all of the building blocks of milk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 83910.0,
      "end_time": 85771.0,
      "text": "then synthesize tiny droplets of fat"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 85771.0,
      "end_time": 89981.0,
      "text": "on structures called  smooth endoplasmic reticula."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 89981.0,
      "end_time": 93500.0,
      "text": "The droplets combine with each other and other molecules"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 93500.0,
      "end_time": 97780.0,
      "text": "and are then expelled and stored in spaces between cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 97780.0,
      "end_time": 101721.0,
      "text": "Mammary glands eventually secrete the milk through the breasts, udders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 101721.0,
      "end_time": 107610.0,
      "text": "or, in the rare case of the platypus,  through ducts in the abdomen."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 107610.0,
      "end_time": 110342.0,
      "text": "Although this process is typically reserved for females,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 110342.0,
      "end_time": 113182.0,
      "text": "in some species, like dayak fruit bats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 113182.0,
      "end_time": 114420.0,
      "text": "goats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 114420.0,
      "end_time": 115322.0,
      "text": "and even cats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 115322.0,
      "end_time": 117612.0,
      "text": "males can also lactate."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 117612.0,
      "end_time": 120782.0,
      "text": "Milk drinkers worldwide consume dairy from buffalo,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 120782.0,
      "end_time": 121591.0,
      "text": "goats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 121591.0,
      "end_time": 122324.0,
      "text": "sheeps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 122324.0,
      "end_time": 123122.0,
      "text": "camels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 123122.0,
      "end_time": 123991.0,
      "text": "yaks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 123991.0,
      "end_time": 124782.0,
      "text": "horses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 124782.0,
      "end_time": 126420.0,
      "text": "and cows."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 126421.0,
      "end_time": 129122.0,
      "text": "Almost all of these species are ruminants,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 129122.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132212.0,
      "text": "a type of mammal with  four-chambered stomachs"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 132212.0,
      "end_time": 134900.0,
      "text": "that yield large quantities of milk."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 134901.0,
      "end_time": 137934.0,
      "text": "Of these, cows were the most  easily domesticated"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 137934.0,
      "end_time": 141696.0,
      "text": "and produce a milk that is both easily separated into cream and liquid"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 141696.0,
      "end_time": 145335.0,
      "text": "and has a similar fat content to human milk."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 145335.0,
      "end_time": 146782.0,
      "text": "In their natural environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 146782.0,
      "end_time": 151303.0,
      "text": "mammals secrete milk on call  for immediate consumption by their young."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 151303.0,
      "end_time": 153852.0,
      "text": "But with the demands of thirsty consumers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 153852.0,
      "end_time": 157656.0,
      "text": "the dairy industry has enlisted methods to step up production,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 157656.0,
      "end_time": 159300.0,
      "text": "enhance shelf life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 159300.0,
      "end_time": 162564.0,
      "text": "and provide a variety of milk products."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 162564.0,
      "end_time": 166873.0,
      "text": "In the dairy, centrifugation machines spin milk at high speeds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 166873.0,
      "end_time": 171822.0,
      "text": "forcing less dense fats to separate from the liquid and float up."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 171822.0,
      "end_time": 173173.0,
      "text": "After being skimmed off,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 173173.0,
      "end_time": 176932.0,
      "text": "this fat, known as butterfat, can be used in dairy products"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 176932.0,
      "end_time": 177673.0,
      "text": "like butter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 177673.0,
      "end_time": 178414.0,
      "text": "cream,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 178414.0,
      "end_time": 179513.0,
      "text": "and cheese."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 179514.0,
      "end_time": 183743.0,
      "text": "Or it can be later added back to  the liquid in varying proportions"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 183743.0,
      "end_time": 186313.0,
      "text": "to yield different fat content milks."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 186313.0,
      "end_time": 193543.0,
      "text": "Full fat milk, sometimes referred to as whole milk, has 3.25% butterfat added"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 193544.0,
      "end_time": 197895.0,
      "text": "compared to 1-2% for low and reduced fat milk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 197895.0,
      "end_time": 200864.0,
      "text": "and less than half a percent  for skim milk."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 200864.0,
      "end_time": 204754.0,
      "text": "To stop reseparation of the fat from the water, or creaming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 204754.0,
      "end_time": 209893.0,
      "text": "the mixture undergoes the high-energy pressurized process of homogenization."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 209894.0,
      "end_time": 214204.0,
      "text": "Before milk hits the shelves, it&#39;s also typically heat treated"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 214204.0,
      "end_time": 216155.0,
      "text": "to reduce its level of microbes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 216155.0,
      "end_time": 217665.0,
      "text": "a government-sanctioned process"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 217665.0,
      "end_time": 222384.0,
      "text": "that raw milk enthusiasts argue  may reduce milk&#39;s nutritional worth."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 222384.0,
      "end_time": 225605.0,
      "text": "Milk spoilage is started by microbes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 225605.0,
      "end_time": 228994.0,
      "text": "which consume and break down  the nutrients in milk."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 228995.0,
      "end_time": 232395.0,
      "text": "That process causes butterfat  to clump together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 232395.0,
      "end_time": 235735.0,
      "text": "leading to a visually unpleasant product."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 235735.0,
      "end_time": 237994.0,
      "text": "And the byproducts of  the microbes&#39; consumption"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 237994.0,
      "end_time": 241835.0,
      "text": "are compounds that taste  and smell nasty."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 241835.0,
      "end_time": 243230.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s a bigger problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 243230.0,
      "end_time": 248500.0,
      "text": "Raw milk can carry microbes that are the sources of deadly diseases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 248500.0,
      "end_time": 251566.0,
      "text": "so in order to kill as many of those microbes as possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 251566.0,
      "end_time": 253476.0,
      "text": "and keep milk fresh longer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 253476.0,
      "end_time": 256668.0,
      "text": "we use a technique called pasteurization."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 256668.0,
      "end_time": 259495.0,
      "text": "One version of this process involves exposing milk"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 259495.0,
      "end_time": 262155.0,
      "text": "to about 30 seconds of high heat."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 262155.0,
      "end_time": 265594.0,
      "text": "Another version,  called ultra-high temperature processing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 265595.0,
      "end_time": 267376.0,
      "text": "or ultra pasteurization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 267376.0,
      "end_time": 273360.0,
      "text": "blasts the milk with considerably higher  temperatures over just a few seconds."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 273360.0,
      "end_time": 276326.0,
      "text": "UHT milk boasts a much longer shelf life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 276326.0,
      "end_time": 278626.0,
      "text": "up to twelve months unrefrigerated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 278626.0,
      "end_time": 282226.0,
      "text": "compared to pasteurized milk&#39;s two weeks in the fridge."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 282226.0,
      "end_time": 285870.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s because the higher temperatures of UHT processing"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 285870.0,
      "end_time": 287647.0,
      "text": "inactivate far more microbes."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 287647.0,
      "end_time": 290580.0,
      "text": "Yet the higher processing temperatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 290580.0,
      "end_time": 294832.0,
      "text": "may adversely affect the nutritional and sensory properties of the milk."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 294832.0,
      "end_time": 297907.0,
      "text": "Ultimately, that choice lies in the consumer&#39;s taste"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 297907.0,
      "end_time": 299688.0,
      "text": "and need for convenience."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 299688.0,
      "end_time": 302670.0,
      "text": "Fortunately, there are many  choices available"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 302670.0,
      "end_time": 308308.0,
      "text": "in an industry that produces in excess  of 840 million tons of products each year."
    }
  ]
}